Myrmecicultor is genus of araneomorph spiders. As of November 2020, it has only one species Myrmecicultor chihuahuensis, and is the only genus in the family Myrmecicultoridae. It is native to the Chihuahuan Desert, from the Big Bend region of Texas to Coahuila and Aguascalientes in Mexico. Collected specimens were associated with three species of harvester ants, Pogonomyrmex rugosus, Novomessor albisetosis, and Novomessor cockerelli, being found in pitfall traps when the ants were most active.